TITLE: Youngkin sets special election to fill Rep. McEachin's seat
SUMMARY: Following the death of late Democratic Rep. A. Donald McEachin, Virginia Governor Glenn Youngkin is setting a special election in order to fill the 4th Congressional seat.

TITLE: Iowa judge rejects Gov. Reynolds' appeal to reinstate fetal heartbeat abortion law
SUMMARY: A judge in Iowa said there is no legal means to reverse a 2019 court decision that blocked the state's fetal heartbeat law from taking effect.

TITLE: Lauren Boebert calls to 'take the temperature down,' focus on policy after narrow midterm win
SUMMARY: Colorado GOP Rep. Lauren Boebert called for the temperature in Washington to go "down" and noted political bomb-throwing won't be her "top focus" in the GOP majority.

TITLE: Vulnerable Montana senator won't commit to re-election bid: 'Retire or lose' says state GOP
SUMMARY: Republicans are hoping to oust Sen. Jon Tester, the only Democrat to hold statewide office in Montana, when his seat is up for grabs in the 2024 elections.

TITLE: WA Gov. Inslee's equity summit tells state agencies 'objectivity,' 'individualism' rooted in 'White supremacy'
SUMMARY: Washington Gov. Jay Inslee's equity summit included a presentation telling state agencies that ideas like "objectivity" and "individualism" are rooted in White supremacy.

TITLE: Vladimir Putin cancels annual press conference as Russia stalls in Ukraine
SUMMARY: Russian President Vladimir Putin canceled his annual year-end press conference for the first time in a decade on Tuesday. Observers say Putin fears growing anti-war sentiment.

TITLE: Colorado election results: Lauren Boebert wins re-election by 546 votes, recount confirms
SUMMARY: Republican Rep. Lauren Boebert narrowly defeated Democrat Adam Frisch in the race for Colorado's 3rd Congressional District, a recount confirmed.

TITLE: Former VP Pence says positive response to autobiography ‘great source of encouragement’ as he mulls 2024 bid
SUMMARY: Former Vice President Mike Pence says that the positive response he highlights he’s receiving from his new autobiography “has been very encouraging” as he weighs a 2024 White House run

TITLE: Biden to sign same-sex marriage bill despite concerns by some progressives
SUMMARY: President Biden will sign the Respect for Marriage Act into law Tuesday, which will require the federal government to recognize same-sex marriages performed in states where they are legal.

TITLE: Gen. Petraeus says Ukraine, military readiness top priorities for NDAA, vax mandate outrage ‘manufactured’
SUMMARY: Former CIA Director Gen. David Petraeus spoke with Fox News Digital about top priorities that should be included in the National Defense Authorization Act.

TITLE: Retired Navy SEAL who is no longer a trans woman has advice for veterans getting VA care: ‘Ask questions’
SUMMARY: A former Navy SEAL who is transitioning back to a man said that other veterans need to take charge of their health care, and said VA needs to spend more time with veterans.

TITLE: Non-binary nuclear waste official charged in multiple luggage thefts departs Department of Energy
SUMMARY: A non-binary Biden administration official who oversaw the nuclear waste policy at the DOE's Office of Nuclear Energy is reportedly out of the job following charges of luggage theft.

TITLE: Biden to establish interagency group, national strategy to counter antisemitism
SUMMARY: President Biden is set to establish an inter-agency group to increase and coordinate U.S. government efforts to counter “antisemitism, Islamaphobia and other related forms of bias and discrimination.”

TITLE: Milking the Clock — In Football, Futball, and Congress
SUMMARY: Los Angeles Rams quarterback Baker Mayfield may not know a lot about how to avert a government shutdown; but Mayfield knows this: you play until the end of the game.

TITLE: Biden invites anti-police nonbinary drag queen to White House: 'F--- the police'
SUMMARY: President Biden extended an invitation to drag queen Marti Cummings to attend a White House event where he will sign the Respect for Marriage Act.

TITLE: GOP plots swing state shake-up to prevent 2024 defeats
SUMMARY: Swing state Republicans are plotting an overhaul of their state parties' leadership structure to ensure the GOP is more competitive in 2024 and beyond.

TITLE: GOP signals investigations, possible subpoenas on COVID origin, domestic extremism monitoring: Rep. Turner
SUMMARY: Ranking Member Rep. Mike Turner told Fox News Digital that there was "unanimous" bipartisan support for two "resolutions of inquiry" that were voted on in committee last week.

TITLE: Biden directed offstage by child after Toys for Tots remarks
SUMMARY: President Biden appeared confused Monday after his speech with Toys for Tots in Arlington, Virginia, and had to be led offstage by a young girl who took his hand.

TITLE: White House says bringing Marine veteran Paul Whelan home is 'as high a priority as the president has'
SUMMARY: The White House said the Biden administration is “bound and determined” to bring Marine veteran Paul Whelan home to the United States; it is “as high a priority as the president has.”

TITLE: Senate tees up one-week funding bill to avert government shutdown
SUMMARY: Congressional lawmakers are rushing to avert a government shutdown, but Democrats and Republicans remain divided over how long to keep the government funded.
